From: BioCheck Build Engineering
Subject: [PATCH] TenniS: include cstdlib for GCC 13 compatibility

The upstream source uses std::malloc and std::free but does not include the
header that declares them. Modern GCC correctly rejects this.

--- a/src/memory/orz/pot.cpp
+++ b/src/memory/orz/pot.cpp
@@
 #include "pot.h"
+#include <cstdlib>
